HEADWORD: Cosmopolitism
<hw>Cos*mop"o*li*tism</hw> <pr>(k?z-m?p"?-l?-t?z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The condition or character of a cosmopolite; disregard of national
or local peculiarities and prejudices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

